# Keep the build context hermetic. Without this, `COPY . .` in the Dockerfile
# drags the host/runner's node_modules into the image, clobbering the clean
# alpine deps stage — when CI runs `npm ci` before `docker build` (as the
# release pipeline does), those are glibc-built native modules (next-swc,
# prisma, ssh2, sharp…) and the musl/alpine build then fails. The image builds
# its own deps in the `deps` stage, so none of this belongs in the context.
node_modules
.next
.git
.github

# Never bake secrets or local state into the image
.env
.env.*
backups
*.log
npm-debug.log*

# Not needed at build/runtime
.vscode
.idea
# The e2e suite tests the image; it doesn't belong inside it.
test
docker-compose.test.yml
e2e-artifacts
*.md
# …except the changelog: the what's-new dialog serves it at runtime
# (Dockerfile COPYs it out of the builder stage).
!CHANGELOG.md
coverage
.DS_Store
